===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Left out of water, stranded on a beach, or in the stocks for repair, or in [[dry dock]].
# Abandoned, stranded, helpless.
# {{lb|en|pejorative}} Associated with the high church (the Church of England and other Anglican traditions, in reference to their "high" political position in England and "dry"/austere mode of worship), as opposed to the "[[low and slow]]" Evangelical party and the "[[broad and shallow]]" broad church.
#* '''1844''', A. H. Maltby, ''The New Englander'', volume 2, [http://books.google.com/books?id=0Y4FAAAAQAAJ&pg=PA321&dq=high+and+dry page 321]:
#*: "There are two recognized parties in the church of England, the old '''High-and-dry''' church party, and the so-called Evangelical. To one or other of these two the Anglo-Catholic must conform."
# {{lb|en|US|slang|of a|sandwich}} With no condiments.

